### emitConstantPool() {#a211d4a615171c1711209d5a362f5aa27}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="void llvm::ARMAsmPrinter::emitConstantPool ()"
  labels = {["inline", "virtual"]}>
Print to the current output stream assembly representations of the constants in the constant pool MCP.

EmitConstantPool - Print to the current output stream assembly representations of the constants in the constant pool MCP.

This is used to print out constants which have been &quot;spilled to memory&quot; by the code generator.

### emitInlineAsmEnd() {#a5e630ae7b9bb8b39e492f7ab7a5f19bb}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>void ARMAsmPrinter::emitInlineAsmEnd (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcsubtargetinfo">MCSubtargetInfo</a> &amp; StartInfo, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcsubtargetinfo">MCSubtargetInfo</a> &#42; EndInfo) const</>}
  labels = {["virtual"]}>
Let the target do anything it needs to do after emitting inlineasm.

This callback can be used restore the original mode in case the inlineasm contains directives to switch modes. <code>StartInfo</code> - the original subtarget info before inline asm <code>EndInfo</code> - the final subtarget info after parsing the inline asm, or NULL if the value is unknown.
